Thomas Kaplan - Wikipedia





















 






Thomas Kaplan

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search



Thomas Kaplan


Born
1962 (age 54–55)


Residence
New York City, New York, US


Nationality
American


Alma mater
BA, MA, PhD Oxford University


Occupation
Investor, conservationist, philanthropist


Net worth
US $ 1.3 billion
(March 2013)[1]


Spouse(s)
Daphne Recanati


Children
three


Parent(s)
Jason Kaplan
Lillian Jean Kaplan


Relatives
Leon Recanati (father-in-law)


Thomas S. Kaplan (born 1962) is an American entrepreneur, natural resources investor, philanthropist and art collector. An admirer of Rembrandt, Kaplan is known as the world's largest private collector of the Dutch master's works.
He is the chairman and chief investment officer of The Electrum Group LLC, a New York City-based investment, advisory and asset management firm with a focus on the natural resources sector.



Contents


1 Early life and education
2 Career
3 Rembrandt and the Old Masters
4 Philanthropy

4.1 Conservation
4.2 Medical research
4.3 Academia and public policy
